<PRE></PRE>

<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=460><tr><td>
<DL><B>
<IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN=BASELINE WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=27 SRC="images/tiny-logo-acij.gif">

		W<FONT SIZE=-1>ELCOME TO THE</FONT> 
		A<FONT SIZE=-1>USTRALIAN</FONT>
		C<FONT SIZE=-1>ENTRE FOR</FONT>
		I<FONT SIZE=-1>NDEPENDENT</FONT> 
		J<FONT SIZE=-1>OURNALISM</FONT></B></A>
		<DL><DO><B><UL>
		<LI><A HREF="ACIJ/ACIJnews.html">News from the ACIJ</A> </B>  Seminars, publications, projects.<B>
	<LI><A HREF="#membership">Getting involved</A></B>  Associate Membership, Corporate Sponsorship.<B>
<LI><A HREF="ACIJ/who.html">Who's who</A></B> at the ACIJ
	</DO></DL></DL></DL>
</td></tr></table>

<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=460><tr><td>
<DL><B>
<IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN=BASELINE WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=27 SRC="images/tiny-logo-acij.gif">
H<FONT SIZE=-1>OT</FONT> T<FONT SIZE=-1>OPICS</FONT> 
</B></A>
<DL><DO><B><UL>
<LI><A HREF="intersections/index.html">INTERSECTIONS WITH ASIA:</A></B> The future of international journalism.
This conference, held in Sydney on November 11th and 12th, 1996 looks at Asia and the Pacific - the fastest growing media markets in the world. Conference proceedings are being placed online as they become available.
<LI><B><A HREF="ACIJ/Crisis/crisis.html">The Crisis in Australian Public Broadcasting</A></B>  The budgetary and ideological attacks on public broadcasting in Australia. Includes ACIJ submission to the current review.
<LI><B><A HREF="ACIJ/Tonga/tonga.html">Jailing of Tongan Journalists</A></B>  The jailings of two journalists and a pro-democracy MP in Tonga shocked the region. Some responses to the jailings, news from the Times of Tonga, a response from the Tongan government and news of their release, plus FLASH: <A HREF="pmw/index.html">Pacific Media Watch</A> details the late November re-arrest of two of the men.
<LI><B><A HREF="gallery/index.html">East Timor Images: 1942 to 1996<BR></A></B></FONT>
Fifty years of Photojournalism on East Timor. Selections from an exhibition of photographs of East Timor recently shown at UTS, and banned from being shown in the Australian Parliament House in October 1996.
<LI><B><A HREF = "acij/Munster.html">George Munster Award for Freelance Journalism</A></B> Australia's only national award for freelance journalists. Background info and details on how to enter for the $1,000 prize. Entries for 1996 award closed on 14th October, 1996. Winner to be announced in early December.
</DO></DL></DL></DL>
</td></tr></table>

<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=460><tr><td>
<DL><B>
<IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN=BASELINE WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=27 SRC="images/tiny-logo-acij.gif">
		ACIJ O<FONT SIZE=-1>NLINE</FONT> 
		P<FONT SIZE=-1>UBLICATIONS</FONT></B></A>
<DL><DO><B><UL><LI><A HREF="reportageindex.html">Reportage Media Bulletin</A></B>  
The ACIJ's ground-breaking magazine on journalism and the media looks behind the headlines. Site includes a full issue of the magazine. Issue Number 7 is available in all major newsagents now.
<LI>
<B><A HREF="snoop/ISSUE5/COVER.HTM">Snoop</A></B> The ACIJ's award-winning magazine of inquiry. See the updated web version.
<LI>
<B><A HREF="UniT_Home.html">Uni Tavur Online</A></B>  The award-winning newspaper published by journalism students at the University of Papua New Guinea's South Pacific Centre for Communication & Information in Development is now on the Web thanks to a joint project of SPCenCIID and the ACIJ. 
<LI>
<B><A HREF="ACIJ/resources.html">Resources</A></B>  The ACIJ has an extensive resource of reports, research guides, training manuals and books of value to journalists. This includes our "Front Page and Beyond" training manuals, since adopted in Australia as the training standard by Fairfax and News Ltd.
<LI><B>
<A HREF="ACIJ/video.html">"Making a Difference"</A> </B>Watch a short video clip from our film, "Making a Difference" - a film about how infotainment news values, such as 'conflict', dominate coverage of Aboriginal and ethnic issues in the Australian media. 
<LI><B>
<A HREF="ACIJ/chomsky.html"> Noam Chomsky's new book</A> 
</B>In his new book, <B>'Powers and Prospects: Reflections on human nature and the social order'</B>, Chomsky challenges predominant views of the worlds of human thought, language, western politics and the media. In September 1996 the book entered the Australian best-seller list for non-fiction at number nine. You can order your copy from the ACIJ Bookshop.
</DO></DL></DL></DL> 
</td></tr></table>

