<TD>
<P><CENTER><B><FONT SIZE="+1">Sydney November11-12, 1996
<P>Presented by The International Media Centre of the<BR>
Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade</FONT></B>
</CENTER>
<P><FONT SIZE="+1">Asia and the Pacific are the fastest growing media markets in the world. The region is being transformed by new technologies, rising affluence, and a growing demand for English language information.
<P>
The conference considers how this is changing the ways we define and practise journalism. The speakers are from South-East Asia, Australia and international media agencies with a focus on the region.</FONT>
</TD></TR>
