<B></B><HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>JAILING OF TONGAN JOURNALISTS</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
 
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<A NAME="top"><IMG WIDTH=475 SRC="/../images/online.gif" ALT="The Online Journalist"></A>
<IMG VSPACE=10 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<td width=20><BR></td><td ALIGN=center>
<H1>JAILING OF TONGAN JOURNALISTS</H1>
</td><td width=10><BR></td>
</tr></table>

<IMG height=2 width=485 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=70><BR></td>
<td width=370>
On 20 September 1996, Kalafi Moala, editor of the "Tonga Times", deputy editor Filokalafi 'Akau'ola, and a Member of Parliament, 'Akilisi Pohiva, were found in contempt of Parliament and sentenced to 30 days in jail. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The decision by the mainly unelected Legislative Assembly, was in regard to the publication in the newspaper's September 4 edition of a planned notice of impeachment intended to have Justice Minister Tupou removed from office for allegedly accepting a Parliamentary allowance while visiting the Atlanta Olympic Games for which he also had no formal permission of the Assembly to attend.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The motion of impeachment had not in fact been tabled as the newspaper report stated. It was finally tabled on September 23, and the Assembly then voted that the Minister has a case to answer. Formal impeachment proceedings may now follow.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
On October 2, the Tongan Parliament was closed until July 1997 by the Cabinet, citing absences and pressure of other business. Accordingly, the impeachment proceedings cannot proceed till then. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
In the meantime, the journalists and the MP remain in the custody of jail authorities. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A NAME="flash">NEWSFLASH!</A><BR>
<A HREF="tonga-free.html">Tongan Journalists Free!</A></B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
October 15, 1996.  A decision handed down by the Supreme Court in Tonga yesterday means that the jailed Tongan journalists are now free. The court ruled that the journalists, jailed for contempt of Parliament on September 20, had been detained illegally. David Robie reports on the decision for the <A HREF="/../cafepacific/resources/david_aspac.html">Asia-Pacific Network</A>.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR><BR>
[The following statements on the Tongan jailings have originated from many organisations . The views expressed should be attributed to the cited groups and indididuals.]

<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-ACIJ.html">ACIJ condemns attack on media freedom in Tonga</A> </B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-PJR.html">Pacific Journalism Review (PJR) protests journalists' jailings</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-IFJ.html">International Federation of Journalists (IFJ) response</A> </B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-Times.html">Message from the Tonga Times to statements of support</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-Gov.html">Response from the Tongan Government to criticism of the</A>
<BR><IMG HSPACE=5 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="tonga-Gov.html">jailings</A></B> 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-RSF.html">Reporters Sans Frontieres response</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-terrorism.html">Asia-Pacific Network reports Tongan government on</A><BR><IMG HSPACE=5 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="tonga-terrorism.html">'media terrorism'</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-PCRC.html">Pacific Concerns Resource Centre, Fiji, response</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-PFIN.html">Pacific Freedom of Information Network response</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-PINA.html">Pacific Islands News Association appeal to king</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-chronicle.html">Tongan Chronicle reports that court appeal to free</A><BR><IMG HSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="tonga-chronicle.html">journalists rejected</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<B>*  <A HREF="tonga-otherweb.html">Other sources of information available on the Web on the</A><BR><IMG HSPACE=5 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="tonga-otherweb.html">Tongan jailings</A></B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
