<B>Pacific Media Watch is a Web site dedicated to issues of ethics <BR>
and accountability, censorship, media freedom and media <BR>
ownership in the Pacific region. Launched in October 1996, PMW is an<BR>
independent group of journalists and media academics.
<br><IMG vspace=2 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
Pacific Media Watch Online, published in partnership with the Australian<BR> Centre for  Independent Journalism, Papua Niugini Nius and Pactok, can be<BR> 
reached at PO Box 9, Annandale 2038, Australia, or <BR>
PO Box 273, University  Post Office, NCD, Papua New Guinea.
<br><IMG vspace=2 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
