<head></head>
<body bgcolor="#000000" text="FFFFFF" link="ffff00" vlink="b0c0f0" alink="ff0000">
<font size="+1">
<center>
<h1><strong>East Timor Images</strong></h1>
<h2>50 Years in photographs</h2></p><br>
<img src="../images/colorbar.gif"></p>
<br><br><br>
<table>
<tr>
<td align="center" valign="middle"><img src="photos/sleepingkidtm.jpg"></td><td></td><td align="center" valign="middle"><img src="photos/starvkidstm.jpg"></td></tr>
<tr>
<td></td><td align="center" valign="middle"> <img src="photos/womanfisttm.jpg"> </td><td></td></tr>
<tr>
<td align="center" valign="middle"><img src="photos/womsoldiertm.jpg"></td><td></td><td align="center" valign="middle"><img src="photos/redberettm.jpg"></td></tr>
</table></p>
<br><br><br><br>

Images of East Timor representing the period 1942 to 1996.</p>

The pictures present only a sample of an exhibition put together by Dr Andrew McNaughton, titled</p><br> <h2>"Betrayed, But Not Beaten"</h2></p><br>

This exhibition was displayed as part of the Oporto Conference in Sydney in June 1996 and has been on display at the New South Wales Parliament building (Sydney) and in Parramatta.  In late 1996 the exhibition will tour Malaysia and the Phillipines.</p>

Photographers whose work was displayed included: Damian Parer, Elaine Briere, Penny Tweedie, Oliver Strewe, Mike Richardson, Peter Rodgers, Jenny Groves, Ross Bird, Steve Cox and Max Stahl, as well as organisations such as Reuters (NY), 'Sydney Morning Herald' and the Melbourne 'Age'.</p>

Enquiries about the exhibition should be directed to Dr Andrew McNaughton, PO Box 751, Darlinghurst  NSW  2010, Australia.</p><br><br>
<table>
<tr>
<td><a href="pixpage.html"><img hspace=6 src="photos/womsmall.jpg">See the Gallery</a></p>
<a href="../index.html"><img hspace=6 src="../images/tiny-logo-acij.gif">Back to the ACIJ Homepage</a></td></tr>
</table></p><br><br>
<hr>
<br>

ACIJ Website Editor: <A HREF="mailto:p.cronau@uts.edu.au">Peter Cronau</A></p>
<Font color="ff0509">Page designed by Rob Taylor</font><br>
October 1996</p>
<img src="../images/spin.gif">
</center>
