<HTML> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<HEAD><TITLE>Reportage</TITLE></HEAD> 
<IMG ALT= REPORTAGE HEIGHT=100  WIDTH=475 Align=Top SRC="/images/reportage.gif">
<P><B>http://acij.uts.edu.au/reportageindex.html</B><P>
<HR>

	<DD>Reportage, the ACIJ's popular media magazine, aims to generate
	discussion 	on 	the nature and role of the media. It features the 	background to 
	the reporting of current stories, the public's struggle to get behind the news, 
	dilemmas facing journalists, developments in the media industry, reviews and news.<p>
	<DD>Reportage has covered controversial topics such as the performance of the media on reporting on intelligence agencies, the influence of advertising 
	on editorial decisions, how the Olympic Games bid was reported, bias 
	in the reporting of Mabo, suppression of news on East Timor and Bougainville, journalists and human rights, internet media, self censorship, PR influence, amongst others. People appearing in Reportage have included John Pilger, Noam Chomsky, Brian Toohey, Wendy Bacon, Chris Masters, Sharon Davis, David Bowman, Liz Jackson, David Robie, and Anna Solomon.<p>
<HR>
<h2>Archive of Reportage</h2>
<dl>
<dt>
<A HREF = "/reportage5/R5contents.html">Reportage 5</A><br>
<dd>
Our web version of the full issue of Reportage 5 is available. <br><br>
</dl><dl>
<dt>
<A HREF = "/reportage6/R6contents.html">Reportage 7</A><br>
<dd>Just released into newsagents is the latest issue - Reportage Media Bulletin, Number 7, Summer 1996/97 edition. We hope to shortly load on the site an abbreviated web version of this new issue, plus a full version of Number 6: Winter 1996. To get your hard copy, you can subscribe, or you can ask for Reportage in major newsagents across Australia, distributed by Gordon & Gotch.
</dl>
<HR>
<H2>Ordering the hard copy of Reportage</H2>
<dl>
<dt>
 <A HREF="backcopies.html">Order now!</A><br>
<dd>Ensure you are getting the full story by subscribing to Reportage. Published twice a year, Reportage is essential reading to all journalists, opinion leaders and those interested in the media and how it works in our society. Back copies of all ACIJ publications, including <B>Reportage</B>, are available.
</dl>
