<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Noam Chomsky's New Book</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<Font size=5>
<B><CENTER>A Special Offer to Web Wanderers of the World!</CENTER><BR></B>
</font>

<IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<table border=0 cellpadding=0><tr>
<td width=220>
<IMG HEIGHT=300 ALIGN=center SRC="/images/chomsky.GIF"> 
</td>
<td width=50><BR></td>
<td width=200 align=center>
<Font size=4>ANNOUNCING THE NEW BOOK BY NOAM CHOMSKY</font>
<BR><p><IMG VSPACE=2 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<B><font size=+3>"Powers and Prospects: Reflections on Human Nature and the Social Order"</B></Font>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR><p>
<Font size=4>AVAILABLE BY ADVANCE ORDER FROM 
THE AUSTRALIAN CENTRE FOR INDEPENDENT JOURNALISM</font><BR><BR><Font size=3>
http://acij.uts.edu.au./ACIJ/chomsky.html</B></font>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG VSPACE=5 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<IMG VSPACE=7 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1><B>EXCLUSIVE SPECIAL OFFER</B><BR>
ADVANCE ORDERS NOW TAKEN FOR THE NEW BOOK BY NOAM CHOMSKY TO BE PUBLISHED IN JUNE 1996.<BR>
ADVANCE ORDERS MUST CLOSE MAY 24 FOR DISPATCH EARLY JUNE.</FONT></CENTER>
<BR><BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B>'Powers and Prospects: <BR>Reflections on Human Nature and the Social Order'
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
By Professor Noam Chomsky</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR><BR>
<font size=+2>"The reason for official secrecy is, as usual, hatred of democracy: fear that the primary enemy, the domestic public, might not appreciate what is being done in their name and with their money."</font>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR><BR>
<BR><IMG HSPACE=6 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif">
<font size=+1>Noam Chomsky has been described as "the world's greatest dissident" and "arguably the most important intellectual alive". For 30 years, his dissident views have alerted an increasingly concerned public to the true nature of power. His perceptive descriptions of how the public is excluded from decision making and policy formation, provide new insights into major events in the world today. 
<BR><IMG HSPACE=6 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif">From East Timor to the Middle East, from the nature of democracy to our place in the natural world, from the intellectual responsibility of writers to anarchic visions, from international politics to the politics of language, 'Powers and Prospects: Reflections on Human Nature and the Social Order' provides a scathing critique of orthodox views, the media and government policy. 
<BR><IMG HSPACE=6 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif">Chomsky lifts the veil of lies diverting the public from knowledge of the heinous acts being committed in their name. He reveals how the 'new' world order is a re-marketing of the same old disorder. Chomsky's refreshingly clear views of the world and the nature of things are supported by a wealth of detail.
<BR><IMG HSPACE=6 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif">The works contained in 'Powers and Prospects' reflect the latest thinking of Chomsky on a broad range of themes. The book is developed from a series of addresses he delivered to sellout audiences on his 1995 visit to Australia.
<BR><IMG HSPACE=6 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif">Noam Chomsky is Professor of Linguistics at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology in Cambridge, USA, and is an internationally acclaimed philosopher, scholar and political activist. His many books include 'The Washington Connection and Third World Fascism', 'Towards a New Cold War', 'The Culture of Terrorism', 'Manufacturing Consent: The Political Economy of the Mass Media', 'Deterring Democracy', 'Year 501: The Conquest Continues', and 'World Orders: Old and New'.
</font><BR><BR>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430 ALIGN=LEFT>
<font size=+1><B><p><CENTER>THE FREE COPIES OF CHOMSKY'S NEW BOOK HAVE BEEN WON</CENTER></B></font>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The three copies of Noam Chomsky's new book, 'Powers and Prospects', have been won in our competition which closed on 10 April 1996.
<BR>The winners are 
Robert Roche from Palmyra in Western Australia; P Taylor, from Brisbane, Australia; and David White from Bradford, England.
<BR>The answer to the question "What did then Foreign Minister Gareth Evans say about Chomsky?" is, of course, Chomsky "should confine himself to linguistics".
<BR>Congratulations to the winners and thanks to all those who entered our competition. We got over 70 replies with lots of late entries too.
<BR>To those who didn't win you can still order your copy of the book by using the form below.
</B>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
