<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Signposts</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="images/signposts.gif"></CENTER><br>
<PRE></PRE>

<center><table border=1 cellpadding=5 width=320><tr><td>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6>Important:</FONT><FONT SIZE=5>  This site is still<BR></CENTER>
<CENTER>under development. <BR></CENTER>
<CENTER>It is anticipated that it<BR></CENTER>
<CENTER>will be launched<BR></CENTER>
<CENTER>in November, 1996.</FONT></CENTER>
</td></tr></table></center>


<A NAME="signposts">
	<DL><B>
		<FONT SIZE=4>S</FONT><FONT SIZE=3>IGNPOSTS</FONT>
		<FONT SIZE=3>TO</FONT> 
		<FONT SIZE=4>R</FONT><FONT SIZE=3>EPORTING</FONT>
		<FONT SIZE=4>A</FONT><FONT SIZE=3>SIA AND THE</FONT>
		<FONT SIZE=4>P</FONT><FONT SIZE=3>ACIFIC</FONT></B></A>
<P>
<DD>Signposts is a "web base" of information, guidelines and resources relevant  to those in the media who report on Asia and the Pacific. The database will attempt to extend existing news agendas by focussing on issues of development and human rights in the region. It will contain information on human rights, community development, politics, economics, social issues, NGO and government  policy and programs, plus basic background information and contacts in countries of the region.<P>
Signposts will be an invaluable resource for journalists, researchers, media educators and journalism students. </DL><P> 
<HR>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG alt=return to ACIJ Homepage BORDER=0 ALIGN=BASELINE WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=27 SRC="images/tiny-logo-acij.gif">Return to ACIJ homepage</A>


