<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>ACIJ Continuing Education Program</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">


<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=230>
<IMG HEIGHT=100 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/images/logo-acij.gif"> <center></td><td width=120><BR></td>
<td>
<Font size=5><B>
Journalism & Media<BR>Short Courses</font><BR>
<Font size=4>ACIJ Continuing Education Program Spring 1996</B></font>
</td></center></tr></table>
<PRE></PRE>

<IMG VSPACE=7 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430 ALIGN=LEFT>
<font size=+1>The Australian Centre for Independent Journalism (ACIJ) runs professional development courses for journalists, writers, researchers and anyone who wants to improve their media skills. All participants receive a course manual and successful participants receive a certificate from the ACIJ and UTS.

<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

As well as courses for individual participants, the ACIJ designs and conducts courses to meet specific organisational needs. Such courses have included journalism skills courses for a public utility, a large television organisation, and a magazine; a course in community publishing for journalists and non-government organisations in Papua New Guinea; and an editing course for a publishing house.
</font>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Feature Writing</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A six-week evening course for anyone who wants to learn how to write features or improve their feature writing skills. Covers profiles, news and in-depth features, interviewing, research, developing sources and surviving as a freelancer.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Tuesday evenings from 12 November to 17 December<BR>
Cost: 		$690
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Sub-editing for Print Journalism</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A four-day course for people who edit articles, put together newsletters or magazines, and/or wish to work as a sub-editor. Includes re-writing copy for different readerships, writing headlines and captions, marking copy, proof reading, avoiding defamation and contempt, and layout and design.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Tuesday to Friday: 3 December to 6 December; 18 to 21 February<BR>
Cost: 		$780
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Scriptwriting for Corporate Video</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A two-day course for journalists, public relations professionals, and anyone who wants to learn how to write scripts for corporate, educational or training videos. Covers what a scriptwriter does, analysing a brief, concept development, writing for the spoken word, and how to present a script for production.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Monday, 25 and Tuesday, 26 November<BR>
Cost: 		$550
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Law for Communicators</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A two-day course to teach participants how to avoid the legal traps in communicating. Includes an introduction to defamation, contempt of court, confidentiality, anti-vilification laws, and a session on dealing with lawyers.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Saturday, 12 October and Saturday, 19 October<BR>
Cost: 		$550 
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Journalism for Organisations</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A two-day course aimed at people who prepare newsletters, journals, journal articles, reports and media releases for their organisations. Includes detailed workshops on news writing, media releases, interviewing techniques, and an introduction to feature writing.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Thursdays and Fridays: 3 & 4 October; 12 & 13 December; 13 & 14 February, 1997<BR>
Cost: 		$550
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Television Journalism</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A two-day course to teach participants the basics of television production and presentation. Includes news and current affairs writing, how to put a news/current affairs story together, video skills, interviewing for TV, voicing and presentation.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Thursday, 28 and Friday, 29 November<BR>
Cost: 		$550
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Travel Writing</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A six-week course for journalists, students and anyone who wants to break into the travel writing arena. Covers planning the trip, developing story ideas, making contacts, different writing styles, managing in the field, how to use pictures, and how and where to sell, and re-sell stories.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Monday evenings, 11 November to 16 December<BR>
Cost:		$750
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Theatre Reviewing</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A three-day course for aspiring theatre reviewers. The course will cover understanding and analysing text and performance, finding the reviewers own voice, the craft of writing a review, developing theatre-related features and profiles, and identifying publishing markets. Participants will attend a play and workshop their reviews in class. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Mondays: 10, 17 & 24 February, 1997<BR>
Cost:		$750
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Internet for Journalists and Researchers</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
A one-day course which will provide participants with all the Internet search and navigational skills they need to research stories or issues in depth.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Dates:		Wednesday, 25 September; Monday, 9 December<BR>
Cost: 		$340
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Teeline Shorthand</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The ACIJ also runs a thirteen-week (one semester) course in Teeline Shorthand, which will be held from March to June next year.</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG vspace=10 hspace=0 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=10 hspace=0 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>For more information on any of these courses, or a customised course for your organisation, call Bonita Mason on (02) 9514 1949, or email: 
<A HREF="MAILTO:B.Mason@hum.uts.edu.au">B.Mason@hum.uts.edu.au</A>.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
To register for a course, complete the attached registration form and send to the ACIJ, PO Box 123, Broadway  NSW  2007; or fax (02) 9281 2976.</B></FONT>

<BR><IMG VSPACE=7 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Who Teaches</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The courses are taught by professional journalists who are also experienced educators.

<BR><IMG VSPACE=7 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Accreditation</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Participants will receive a certificate from the University of Technology, Sydney's Australian Centre for Independent Journalism. Certificates will only be issued to participants who complete all workshops satisfactorily.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=450>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=430>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>The Australian Centre for Independent Journalism</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The ACIJ is a non-profit organisation based at the Broadway Campus of the University of Technology, Sydney. It administers the University's Master of Arts in Journalism program and a Graduate Certificate in Journalism. It is also involved in developing and promoting independent, critical and investigative journalism. Throughout the year the ACIJ designs and conducts short courses in journalism as part of its commitment to fostering journalism of the highest standard.

<BR><IMG VSPACE=7 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Courses to suit all needs</B></FONT>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=1 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The ACIJ also designs and delivers journalism education courses tailored to meet specific organisational needs. Courses have included a journalism skills course for a large public utility, an editing course for a publishing house and a journalism course for producers in a large television organisation. Please call us if you are interested in discussing a special course for your organisation.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

