<!--Begin Body Table-->
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 WIDTH=360>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><P></TD>
<TD>
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE="+3"><A NAME="ARASU">Conference</A> Speakers</FONT></B>
</CENTER>
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<FONT SIZE="+1">
<B>Ms Siva ARASU</B> is head of the Editorial Training Unit at Singapore Press
Holdings and plans and organises the professional development of the company's
journalists. During 15 years at SPH, she has worked in positions in all the
English language newspapers published by the company. <A NAME="BACON">Before</A> that she worked
for Singapore Business and the Business Times.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Associate Professor Wendy BACON</B> is one of Australia's best known
investigative journalists. Head of the Department of Social Communication and
Journalism at the University of Technology, Sydney, she is co-convenor of the
Signposts Web project. <A NAME="CASIMIR">Funded</A> by Aus-AID the project is an internet research
tool for journalists and journalism students covering the region.<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Jon CASIMIR</B> is a journalist with the Sydney Morning Herald and editor of
the Sydney Morning Herald web site. <A NAME="DIXIT">He</A> is also author of <i>Postcards from the
Net</i> a travel guide to cyberspace.<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Kunda DIXIT</B> is a Nepalese journalist who is Regional Director for the
Asia-Pacific for the newsagency Inter Press Service in Manila.  <A NAME="KELLY">He</A> has also
been a BBC correspondent at the United Nations in New York and a reporter in
Kathmandu.<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Paul KELLY</B> is editor in chief of The Australian. One of Australia's best
known political reporters, he is also the author of several books on political
figures and events. <A NAME="LOCSIN">During</A> his time at the The Australian, he has been engaged
in increasing the reporting of Asian affairs.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Teodoro L. LOCSIN jr</B>., a well known Philippines commentator on public
affairs, is also editor in chief and publisher of the daily newspaper Today,
executive editor of the weekly magazine Philippines Free Press, and presenter
of the weekly current affairs television program Assignment. <A NAME="MAK">Mr</A> Locsin was
educated in the Philippines and the United States. He was Minister of
Information in the Aquino Government.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Ms Yin-ting MAK</B> is chairperson of the Hong Kong Journalists' Association.
After training in Hong Kong and the United Kingdom, <A NAME="MENZIES">she</A> has worked on the Hong
Kong Daily News, the Tin Tin Daily News and is currently Senior Reporter at
Radio Television Hong Kong.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Hugh MENZIES</B> is a specialist in international business journalism.  His
background includes the New York Times and Business Week and he has been
International Business Editor of Fortune.  <A NAME="O'LOUGHLIN">He</A> is now a consulting editor with
recent projects for Forbes, International Business, and the Financial Post of
Canada.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Peter O'LOUGHLIN</B> is the Bureau Chief at the Associated Press news
service in Sydney. <A NAME="SULAIMAN">A</A> correspondent in the Vietnam War, he has experience in
wire service reporting from Morse code to satellite links.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Ziandoor SULAIMAN</B> is executive Editor of the Malaysian Newsagency,
Bernama. During 22 years with Bernama, he has served as bureau chief/
correspondent in Jakarta and Manila, news editor with the domestic news
service, assistant editor of the general news service, and editor of the
corporate information service. <A NAME="TAPTIM">He</A> is also vice-president of the National Press
Club of Malaysia and Malaysia's representative at the Asian Media Information
and Communication Centre.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Tulsathit TAPTIM</B> is Deputy Editor of the Nation, a national Thai
newspaper.  <A NAME="TOOHEY">The</A> uniquely positioned free press in Thailand makes the Nation one
of the most influential English language newspapers in the region.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Brian TOOHEY</B> is one of Australia's leading columnists. Specialising in
politics and business matters, he is the author of a number of books. <A NAME="WATSON">A</A> former
editor of the National Times, he established its reputation for investigative
journalism.
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr Trevor WATSON</B> is head of Current Affairs at ABC Radio. <A NAME="WILSON">He</A> is one of the
ABC's most experienced foreign correspondents reporting on Asia and the
Pacific. 
<br><IMG vspace=8 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<B>Mr David WILSON</B>, International Training Manager, Bloomberg Business News,
has been with Bloomberg since 1990 as a stock Market Reporter, the inaugurator
of its US company news coverage, first chief of its Princeton news bureau, and
New York bureau chief. He has also worked for Dow Jones.</FONT>
</TD></TR>
