<B></B><HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>SUBMISSION TO REVIEW OF ABC FUNCTIONS</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
 
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<A NAME="top"><IMG WIDTH=475 SRC="/../images/online.gif" ALT="The Online Journalist"></A>
<IMG VSPACE=10 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<td width=20><BR></td><td ALIGN=center>
<H1>SUBMISSION TO MANSFIELD REVIEW OF ABC FUNCTIONS</H1>
<H2>Glynn Davis, Jennifer Craik and The Public Service Broadcasting Research Group</H2></center>
<H3>19 September 1996</H3>
</td><td width=10><BR></td></tr></table>

<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>


<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<B>Submission sections:</B>

<BR><IMG VSPACE=3 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<NOBR>[Preamble] <A HREF="ABC-Principles.html">[Principles]</A> <A HREF="ABC-Programming.html">[Programming]</A> <A HREF="ABC-Structure.html">[Structure]</A> <A HREF="ABC-Funding.html">[Funding]</A> <A HREF="ABC-Recommend.html">[Recommendations]</A></NOBR>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430><FONT SIZE=+1>
<B>Section 1. Preamble</B>

<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

We present this joint submission as academics with professional and personal interests in the future of the ABC. The Public Service Broadcasting Research Group (PSBRG) is a University-based research group which began a process of constructive analysis of the ABC well before the announcement of this review. This project began when there was very little academic debate about public service broadcasting. The PSBRG consists of Professor Elizabeth Jacka, Dr Helen Wilson, Dr Gay Hawkins and Maureen Burns. For the purposes of this submission the PSBRG has been joined by Associate Professor Glyn Davis and Associate Professor Jennifer Craik, well respected academics from the Australian Key Centre for Cultural and Media Policy, who have published widely on broadcasting issues. 

<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

We strongly object to the implementation of severe and debilitating cuts prior to the Review, while acknowledging that the organisation of the ABC could be streamlined subject to clear agreement about aims and priorities. We also strongly object to the 'private' nature of the review. The ABC is arguably the most significant part of Australia's cultural, social and political life, and it has been so for 64 years. To deny public participation in an open review shows an extraordinary disrespect for the high regard in which Australians hold the ABC.

<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

We thus urge you to open the findings of the review to public consideration and debate. The views of the various communities of interest in Australia, (who are after all the funders and the audiences of the ABC ) should not be ignored. 

<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

In particular we urge you to achieve consensus with ABC Management, so that any agreed changes are implemented effectively. As we suggest later, this consensus could be formalised in a seven yearly agreement between the ABC and Government.</FONT>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<CENTER>
