<B></B><HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>THE PUBLIC  BROADCASTER AND CIVIL SOCIETY</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
 
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<A NAME="top"><IMG WIDTH=475 SRC="/../images/online.gif" ALT="The Online Journalist"></A>
<IMG VSPACE=10 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<td width=20><BR></td><td>
<CENTER><H1>THE PUBLIC  BROADCASTER<BR>
AND CIVIL SOCIETY</H1></CENTER>
<H3>
The Women's Economic Think Tank<BR>
WETTANK<BR>
PO Box 675, Glebe NSW 2037, Sydney<BR>
Phone/Fax 02 9552 3698
<BR><IMG VSPACE=3 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Prepared By Eva Cox with assistance from Marian Robinson </H3>
</td><td width=10><BR></td></tr></table>

<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<B>Submission sections:</B>

<BR><IMG VSPACE=3 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<CENTER>[Changing Australia] <A HREF="Cox-02.html">[Political correctness and balance]</A> <A HREF="Cox-03.html">[The agora or forum]</A><BR>
<A HREF="Cox-04.html">[The ABC is not cultural spakfilla]</A> <A HREF="Cox-05.html">[The metros]</A> <A HREF="Cox-06.html">[Radio National (RN)]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-07.html">[Social Capital and the ABC]</A> <A HREF="cox-08.html">[The displeased piper's wanted tunes]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-09.html">[The ABC too timid with alternative views?]</A> <A HREF="cox-10.html">[Some proposals for changes]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-mr01.html">[Marian Robinson]</A> <A HREF="cox-mr02.html">[A two day listening sample]</A></CENTER>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430><FONT SIZE=+1>
<B>Changing Australia</B>

<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

The past two decades in particular have reflected a more diverse Australia, with moves away from a unified identity of assimilation based on British heritage. At the same time, there have been two significant moves in technology and ideology. In the first, the growth of multi media has allowed for more diversity and narrowcast choice options for minority groups. The second has seen a movement in public policy away from the assumptions of further growth of Government for all, and a move towards selective and
targeted Government services.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Therefore a review of the ABC and its charter must take into account both the ability of some groups to access and presumably pay for minority services, and the move away from public sector provision of services which can be provided by the markets. The latter view works within an ideological framework that is flawed and it is within those flaws and omissions much of this submission is placed.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
When the ABC was set up by the Lyons Government in 1932 during the Depression, it was to provide a national broadcaster because the commercial services did not and would not provide the links needed to make us a nation. While the nineties are not the thirties, there are certain similarities which need to be taken into account.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The depression and the rise of extremist political views led to world war. The post war welfare state and development of public sector services, in part, recognised the need for social cohesion and senses of belonging. The present economic situation and some of its political consequences, have undermined some of the presumed certainties of the past four decades.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
There are fewer stable and long term jobs, fewer areas offering lifetime careers and a diminished public support ethos. We often work in many places, part time or casually and more and more of us are working from home. Those in full time jobs work more hours and we spend substantial time commuting.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
There has been a greater emphasis on individualism and rights and less on collectivity and responsibilities.  Changes in gender roles and in workforce participation have altered roles within and between families and communities and the lower birthrate and ageing of the population means changes in living patterns and social connections.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Recognition of the problems we have caused for indigenous Australians and the growth of proportions of those from non anglo backgrounds change the social relations and cultures of Australia. We are a diverse collection of peoples and lifestyles with fewer icons in common and less opportunity for becoming familiar with the new and strange.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
We have also been and are still a relatively tolerant country. While we are still racist and often unaware of our own prejudices, we have moved a long way from white Australia, banning blacks from swimming pools and beating up 'reffos'. These were all present when  I grew up here in the 40's and 50's. It has taken considerable effort to create a social climate in which scapegoating of minority groups is seen as unacceptable. We need to look at what is happening in parts of Europe and the USA as warnings of the consequences of loss of social cohesion, change and insecurity where there is no overarching sense of communality.
</FONT>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="#top">[Return to top]</A>
<A HREF="Cox-02.html">[Next section]</A></CENTER>

<CENTER>[Changing Australia] <A HREF="cox-02.html">[Political correctness and balance]</A> <A HREF="cox-03.html">[The agora or forum]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-04.html">[The ABC is not cultural spakfilla]</A> <A HREF="cox-05.html">[The metros]</A> <A HREF="Cox-06.html">[Radio National (RN)]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-07.html">[Social Capital and the ABC]</A> <A HREF="cox-08.html">[The displeased piper's wanted tunes]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-09.html">[The ABC too timid with alternative views?]</A> <A HREF="cox-10.html">[Some proposals for changes]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-mr01.html">[Marian Robinson]</A> <A HREF="cox-mr02.html">[A two day listening sample]</A></CENTER>
</td></tr></table>

