<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=485 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<B>ACIJ condemns attack on media freedom in Tonga
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
 The following information was released on 23 September by the Australian Centre for Independent Journalism. Copies were forwarded to His Royal Majesty King Taufa'ahau Tupou of Tonga, and His Excellency Prime Minister Baron Vaea of Tonga.</B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=2 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<CENTER><H2>CONDEMNATION OF ATTACK<BR> ON MEDIA FREEDOM IN TONGA</H2></CENTER> 

The jailing of two journalists and an MP whistleblower in Tonga in September is a backward step for press freedom in the Pacific, says the Australian Centre for Independent Journalism. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
"Governments everywhere should resist the tempation to interfere in the role of the media in bringing information to the public, no matter how unfavourable that information may be," says Mr Peter Cronau, Editorial Director of the ACIJ.
"The ACIJ calls for the immediate release from jail of the journalists and the MP."
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The three were jailed following the publication in the weekly Times of Tonga on September 4 of details of an untabled impeachment motion to the Legislative Assembly alleging misconduct by Justice Minister Tevita Tupou. Mr Tupou is alleged to have visited the Atlanta Olympics without the formal permission of the Assembly and to have received the daily allowance for attending parliamentary sessions despite having been out of the country. The journalists, Times editor and publisher Kalafi Moala and his deputy editor, 'Filokalafi 'Akau'ola, and the MP, 'Akilisi Pohiva, have each been jailed for 30 days for contempt of parliament. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Last month the Tongan government refused entry to an Agence France-Presse news reporter to cover a regional media conference, allegedly for previous critical reporting.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
"The publics' right to information is paramount to any passing embarrassment that may be felt by government," says Mr Cronau. "The details of the allegations about a pending call to sack a parliamentarian should be able to be discussed by the public.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
"The international ethics code for journalists requires respect for the right of the public to truth as every journalist's first duty. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
"The Assembly's decision to jail the three is another worrying signal to Tonga's pro-democracy movement that the road to democracy in Tonga promises to be a rocky one."
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Tonga's parliament is made up of a 28-member Legislative Assembly dominated by 19 unelected representatives of Tonga's noble families plus nine publicly elected representatives. Tonga's hereditary monarch, King Taufa'ahau Tupou IV, appoints and chairs a Privy Council of nine unelected ministers.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The jailed MP, 'Akilisi Pohiva, leads the Democracy Party which in 1996 won a majority of the nine elected seats of parliament. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The ACIJ's call comes as a chorus of criticism spreads across the Pacific from media associations including Reporters Sans Frontiers, the International Federatiopn of Journalists, Pacific Journalism Review, Pacific Islands Broadcasting Association, Pacific Islands News Association, Pacific Freedom of Information Network.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<B>Peter Cronau<BR>
Editorial Director, ACIJ<BR>
(61 2) 9514 2482<BR> <A HREF="MAILTO:p.cronau@uts.edu.au">
p.cronau@uts.edu.au</A><BR>
23 September, 1996</B>

</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=485 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

