</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=485 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430><FONT SIZE=+1>
<B>Pacific Journalism Review protests journalists' jailings
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
 The editorial board of the <B>Pacific Journalism Review</B> has forwarded the following letter to the Prime Minister of Tonga. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<B>Prime Minister<BR>
Prime Minister's Office<BR>
Kingdom of Tonga<BR>
Fax: (676) 23888</B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=10 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<CENTER><H2>RELEASE IMPRISONED JOURNALISTS</H2></CENTER>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Your Excellency
<BR><IMG VSPACE=4 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
We urge your Parliament to release without delay the two imprisoned journalists - Taimi 'o Tonga editor Kalafi Moala and deputy editor Filokalafi 'Akau'ola - and Member of Parliament 'Akilisi Pohiva. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The action taken against the three people for alleged contempt of Parliament is draconian and unbecoming of a nation that has a Constitution guaranteeing under Clause 7 "there shall be freedom of speech and the press".
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
We note that Mr 'Akau'ola had already been detained by authorities in February amid widespread international condemnation and an Agence France Presse correspondent was barred from attending a regional media convention in Nuku'alofa last month for alleged critical reporting. We regard the latest action as yet a further unwarranted attempt to intimidate the news media in Tonga.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Article 19 of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights says, "Everyone has the right to freedom of opinion and expression; this right includes freedom to hold opinions without interference and to seek, receive and impart information and ideas through any media and regardless of frontiers." 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=10 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<B>Sincerely
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
David Robie<BR>
Editor, PJR<BR>
23 September 1996</B>
</FONT>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=485 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

