<B></B><HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>JAILING OF TONGAN JOURNALISTS</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
 
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<A NAME="top"><IMG WIDTH=475 SRC="/../images/online.gif" ALT="The Online Journalist"></A>
<IMG VSPACE=10 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<td width=20><BR></td><td ALIGN=center>
<H1>International Federation of Journalists (IFJ) response</H1>
</td><td width=10><BR></td></tr></table>

<IMG height=2 width=485 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="tonga-free.html"><B>[Tongan Journalists Free!]</B></A><BR>
<A HREF="tonga.html">[Jailing of Tongan Journalists]</A>  
<A HREF="tonga-ACIJ.html">[ACIJ condemns attack]</A>  
<A HREF="tonga-PJR.html">[PJR protests]</A>  
<A HREF="tonga-IFEX.html">[IFEX response]</A><BR>  
[IFJ response]  
<A HREF="tonga-Times.html">[Message from Tonga Times]</A>  <A HREF="tonga-Gov.html">[Response from the Tongan Government]</A><BR> 
<A HREF="tonga-RSF.html">[RSF response]</A>  
<A HREF="tonga-terrorism.html">['Media terrorism']</A>  
<A HREF="tonga-PCRC.html">[PCRC, Fiji, response]</A>
<A HREF="tonga-PFIN.html">[PFIN response]</A><BR>
<A HREF="tonga-PINA.html">[PINA appeal to king]</A>  
<A HREF="tonga-chronicle.html">[Tongan Chronicle report]</A>  
<A HREF="tonga-otherweb.html">[Other Web sources of information]</A><BR>
<A HREF="tonga-what.html">[What you can do]</A>
</CENTER>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=485 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<B>The following note was sent to King Taufa'ahau Tupou of Tonga.</B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR> 
<FONT SIZE=+1>
<CENTER><B>International Federation of Journalists Protest on Tongan Jailings</B></CENTER> 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The International Federation of Journalists, the World's largest organisation of journalists, representing more than 400,000 journalists in 95 countries, is dismayed at the jailing of two journalists and one journalist Member of Parliament in Tonga for contempt of Parliament for reporting impeachment of a cabinet member prior to the charge being heard by Parliament.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
On behalf of the regional office of the IFJ, I write to condemn the jailing of these three journalists. This act of punishment is a clear violation of freedom of expression and opinion.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Given the widespread anxiety of human rights organisations and journalist colleagues in the Asia-Pacific region, I hope you will intervene to release unconditionally those journalists that have been jailed. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The IFJ also asks you to intervene to guarantee the rights of journalists in Tonga, who belong to our member organisation, the Pacific Journalists Association.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
We are concerned that this attempt to punish and intimidate journalists and to impose systems of media control are an offence to democracy and undermine the capacity of people to participate openly in society. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
We hope that you will take action to ensure the highest respect for freedom of expression within the institutions of the kingdom of Tonga. 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
I have had the opportunity of meeting personally one of the arrested, MP 'Akilisi Pohiva, who represented Tongan journalists at the Pacific Journalists Association meeting in Suva in 1993 and the IFJ Asia-Pacific meeting in Sydney in 1995.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<B>Christopher Warren<BR>
Senior Vice-President<BR>
International Federation of Journalists<BR>
24 September 1996<BR>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Contact: MEAA Tel: (612) 93330999 FAX: (612) 9333 0933 </B>
</FONT>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=485 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

