</DOCHDR>
<html>
<head><title> Pacific Media Watch: ACIJ</title></head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<HR>
<TD width=475 align=left>
<IMG SRC="../images/pmwlogo.gif" WIDTH=100> <Font size=6>Pacific Media Watch</Font 6>
<h1>ACIJ rejects Bougainville claim</h1>
<Font size=3><B>PMW19: Pacific Media Watch: 22 November 1996
<P>
Title -- M66 MEDIA: ACIJ rejects Bougainville claim
Date -- 22 November 1996
Origin -- Pacific Media Watch
Source -- PMW</B>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
The Australian Centre for Independent Journalism has rejected claims of
censorship over a Bougainville article written by Sydney-based freelance
journalist Max Watts,
<P>
Watts and supporters have distributed their claims widely by the Internet.
<P>
But ACIJ director Alan Knight has responded to a letter from the
Bougainville Freedom Movement by rejecting the claims.
<P>
Watts had claimed that an article about Bougainville television news
coverage had been censored because it was not published in Reportage Media
Bulletin, a magazine devoted to media issues.
<P>
However, the article was instead published earlier this month on ACIJ's
website, The Online Journalist - on the Pacific Media Watch page
under the title <A HREF="bougno.html">No news on Bougainville</A>. 
<P>
"I told Mr Watts that we would place his article on our home page which has
an international readership, in a section specifically related to Pacific
matters," Knight said.
<P>
"Clearly this is not suppression of information, merely an editorial
decision to run the material in an appropriate place."<BR>
