<head><title> Pacific Media Watch: Coma</title></head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<HR>
<TD width=475 align=left>
<IMG SRC="../images/pmwlogo.gif" WIDTH=100> <Font size=6>Pacific Media Watch</Font 6>
<h1>East Timor journalist in coma after attack in Dili</h1>
<Font size=3><B>PMW17: Radio Australia: 19 November 1996
<P>
Title -- M65 MEDIA: East Timor journalist in coma
Date -- 19 November 1996
Origin -- Pacific Media Watch
Source -- Radio Australia, 8:09 AEDT, 18/11/96
Copyright -- RA
Status -- Unabridged
<P>
<HR>
<P>
EAST TIMOR JOURNALIST IN COMA AFTER ATTACK IN DILI</B>
<P>   
An East Timorese journalist has fallen into a coma after being attacked by
eight-men in the capital, Dili.
<P>
Police say Gaudensius Mau, who works for a Jakarta-based newspaper, was
beaten near a police dormitory.
<P>
Police chief, Lieutenant Colonel Beno Kilapong, says the identity and
motive of the attackers is still unknown.
<P>
In the past week, tension has mounted over an interview given by East
Timor's Roman Catholic Bishop, Carlos Belo, to a German magazine.
<P>
The bishop was quoted as saying that Indonesian troops had treated the East
Timorese people like dogs after invading the former Portuguese colony in
1975.<BR>
