<head><title> Pacific Media Watch: Indonesian journalist murdered</title></head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<HR>
<TD width=475 align=left>
<IMG SRC="../images/pmwlogo.gif" WIDTH=100> <Font size=6>Pacific Media Watch</Font 6>
<h1>Indonesian journalist murdered</h1>
<Font size=3><B>PMW20: INDONESIAN JOURNALIST MURDERED
<P>
Title -- Indonesian journalist murdered
Date -- 24 November 1996
Origin -- Reportage Media Bulletin, Number 7, Summer 1996/97
Source -- Peter Cronau, 18/11/96 
<P>
<HR>
<P>
INDONESIAN JOURNALIST MURDERED</B>
<P>
In Indonesia, a crusading investigative journalist has been murdered apparently for articles he has published on government corruption and land disputes.<P>
Fuad Muhammad Syafruddin, a correspondent for the Yogyakarta daily 'Bernas', was fatally beaten in his home on August 13.<P>
Syafruddin died from injuries sustained during a beating by two unidentified men who fled on a motorcycle immediately after the attack.<P>
The men visited Syafruddin's house and beat him with iron bars inflicting serious injuries to his head and stomach. <P>
Syafruddin was transferred to the intensive care unit of a Catholic hospital in Yogyakarta, but never regained consciousness. He died in the hospital three days later. <P>
According to local sources, Syafruddin's murder may be related to his articles on land disputes and government corruption in Bantul, the Yogyakarta suburb that he covered for 'Bernas'.<P>
The US-based Committee to Protect Journalists has written to President Suharto to express alarm over the murder. <P>
The CPJ called on the Indonesian leader to order a complete investigation into Syafruddin's death as well as public disclosure of the investigation's findings.<P>
Further details of the killing have now appeared in current issue of 'TAPOL Bulletin', the magazine of the UK-based Indonesian human rights watchdog, TAPOL.<P>
<P>
<Font size=1> 1996 Reportage and Pacific Media Watch.<BR>
http://acij.uts.edu.au/pmw/ Contact: <A HREF="MAILTO:niusedita@pactok.net">niusedita@pactok.net</A></FONT 1>
</table></table>
