<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>South Pacific Centre for Communication ... (SPCenCIID)</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#70DBDB" alink="#8c7853" vlink="#006600"> <CENTER><A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/UniT_SPCenCIID.html"><IMG ALT="SPCenCIID" ALIGN=TOP SRC="images/Samlogo.gif" WIDTH=100></A></CENTER> <HR><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><TD width= 200></TD><td align=left> http://acij.uts.edu.au/UniTavur/UniT/SPCenCIID/about.html</td><tr></table>
<HR>
<P>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr><td>
<Font size=3>South Pacific Centre for Communication and Information in Development</Font size=3><P>
<A NAME="Development"><Font size=7>Development communications</Font size=7></A><P>
The South Pacific Centre for Communication and Information in Development (SPCenCIID) of the University of Papua New Guinea has taken on a pioneering role in development communication and research in the region.
<P>
Located at the Waigani campus of the University of Papua New Guinea, SPCenCIID  combines the resources of Library and Information Studies and Journalism Studies. 
<P>
It reflects the trend in media study schools internationally to emphasise 'communications' -- combining journalism with public relations, mass communications, television, filmmaking and intercultural studies. Development communication is also a priority. 
<P>
Among resources published by SPCenCIID is the fortnightly newspaper <A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/UniT_Home.html">Uni Tavur</A>; a media and communications journal, <A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/PJR/">Pacific Journalism Review</A>; a daily website and email news service, <A HREF="http://www.pactok.net.au/docs/nius/">Niuswire</A>; a quarterly communications newsletter, <B>Ita Diba</B> and a comprensive new text book on mass media in the region: <A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/cafepacific/resources/david_books.html">Nius Bilong Pasifik: Mass Media in the Pacific.
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=100 SRC="images/Nius.gif"></CENTER>
</A>
<P>
<HR>
<A HREF="#Development"><IMG WIDTH=30 ALIGN=BOTTOM  SRC="images/Samlogo.gif"></A> <a name="INDEX"><Font size=4><strong>Index:</A>
<P>
