<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/cafepacific/resources/david.html">David Robie</A>, lecturer in journalism (print media). He is currently on media research attachment with the Australian Centre of Independent Journalism, UTS. 
<P>
<LI><B>Sorariba Nash</B>, lecturer in journalism (broadcast media). He is currently studying for a masters' degree at Cardiff University.</UL></Font>
<P>
<HR>
<A HREF="#Index"><IMG WIDTH=30 ALIGN=BOTTOM  SRC="images/Samlogo.gif"></A> <Font size=4><B><A NAME="STUDENT">Student Awards</A></B></Font>
<P>
<Font size=3><UL><LI><B>PNG/NZ Journalism Student of the Year Award:</B><BR>
Since 1994, the NZ High Commission in Port Moresby has sponsored an annual award for the best all-round Journalism Student of the Year Award. Winners:<BR>
<B>1994: Kiery Manassah</B> (Vanuatu)<BR>
<B>1995: </B>Joint<B> Theresa Bossin</B> (editor of <B>Uni Tavur</B>, PNG); <B>Kevin Pamba</B> (PNG)<BR>
<P>
<LI><B>1995: Uni Tavur</B> won the PNG/PINA <B>Pacific Media Awards Special Award for Best Student/Community Newspaper.
<P>
<LI>1995: Uni Tavur</B> won the Journalism Education Association (JEA of Australia, NZ and the Pacific) <B>Ossie Award for Best Regular Student Newspaper</B></UL>.
<P>
