<head><title>Cafe Pacific: David's Notebook</title></head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FF6EC7">
<A HREF="../index.html"><IMG SRC="../images/David3.jpeg" width=100></A>
<HR>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=450><tr>
<TD width 200><TD align=left>http://acij.uts.edu.au/cafepacific/resources/david.html
</table>
<HR>
<Font size=7><B>David's Notebook</B></Font size=7>
<H2>Journalist, journalism educator and author</H2>
<P>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>Hi, I'm <B>David Robie</B> and welcome to my home page. I'm an award-winning New Zealand author and journalist who has specialised in reporting Pacific development and political issues, and a media consultant. At the moment, I'm teaching in Papua New Guinea.<P>

For the record, I've edited or been senior editorial executive on newspapers in Australia, France, Kenya, New Zealand and South Africa. I'm also the author of seven books -- including <A HREF="david_books.html">Nius Bilong Pasifik: Mass Media in the Pacific</A> and two others used as texts at the University of Papua New Guinea.<P>

I currently lecture in print journalism at UPNG and have revamped the journalism training newspaper <A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/UniT_Home.html">Uni Tavur</A> as a professional tabloid. For the past three years I have edited <A HREF="index.html">Pacific Journalism Review</A>. Also, check out our <A HREF="http://www.pactok.net/docs/nius"> Niuswire</A> news service.
<P>
<H3><UL>
<LI><A HREF="david_address.html">Address</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="david_aspac.html">Asia-Pacific Network</A><P><LI><A HREF="david_books.html">Books</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.pactok.net/docs/nius">Niuswire</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/UniT_Home.html"><IMG SRC="http://acij.uts.edu.au/UniTavur/images/Smlcover-10-95.gif" WIDTH=100 ALT="Uni Tavur cover"><BR>
Uni Tavur</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="david_who.html">Who's Who</A></UL></H3><P>
<Font size=1>Copyright  David Robie 1996</Font size=1><P>
