<HEAD><TITLE>SUBMISSION TO REVIEW OF ABC FUNCTIONS</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
 
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<A NAME="top"><IMG WIDTH=475 SRC="/../images/online.gif" ALT="The Online Journalist">
</A><IMG VSPACE=10 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<td width=20><BR></td><td ALIGN=center>
<H1>SUBMISSION TO MANSFIELD REVIEW OF ABC FUNCTIONS</H1>
</td><td width=10><BR></td></tr></table>

<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<B>Submission sections:</B>

<BR><IMG VSPACE=3 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<NOBR><A HREF="ABC-Preamble.html">[Preamble]</A> <A HREF="ABC-Principles.html">[Principles]</A> <A HREF="ABC-Programming.html">[Programming]</A> <A HREF="ABC-Structure.html">[Structure]</A> <A HREF="ABC-Funding.html">[Funding]</A> [Recommendations]</NOBR>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430><FONT SIZE=+1>
<B>Section 6. Recommendations</B>

<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

1.	that the ABC should retain and develop its present provision of programming for diverse groups;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
2.  that the ABC should be free of advertising and sponsorship;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
3.  that the ABC provide an independent, accurate, quality News and Current Affairs services to the entire population 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
4.  that the ABC should be able to participate in any 'type' of programming which addresses particular communities in Australia;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
5.  that the ABC should aim for 'quality programming' but that notions of 'quality' should not create a hierarchy of genres or taste communities;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
6.	that all Radio networks (including Radio Australia) should be extended as fully separate services which are low cost broadcasting activities and which address the needs of specific and diverse audiences; 
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
7.	that the ABC should meet its regional imperative with more regard to regional communities than to State boundaries, and that such considerations should be reflected in the reorganisation of management structures;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
8.	that, in order to provide certainty for Parliament, the Corporation, and the public, there should be a detailed 5 or 7 year agreement between the ABC and government;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
9.  that the ABC should make a distinction between production and distribution functions, and that the results of these distinctions may differ in radio and television, and/or across genres;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
10. that the ABC should adapt the purchaser/provider model of Channel 4 in the UK to the specific needs of Australian broadcasting;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
11. that ABC Television is overcapitalised, and that the symbolic presence of studios in every capital city, besides being financially unsustainable, may prevent a greater level of participation by independent regional program makers, and that, following from the above, interstate television studios should be sold, and that studio time should be bought as required from commercial studios, or by greater co-operation with radio stations;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
12. that Australia Television should be funded on the same basis as Radio Australia; this means either voting it extra funds or closing it down;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
13. that the ABC should develop its online presence as an adjunct to its radio and television services;
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
14. that SBS should remain an autonomous entity.
</FONT>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

