<B></B><HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>THE PUBLIC  BROADCASTER AND CIVIL SOCIETY</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
 
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<A NAME="top"><IMG WIDTH=475 SRC="/../images/online.gif" ALT="The Online Journalist"></A>
<IMG VSPACE=10 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
<td width=20><BR></td><td ALIGN=center>
<H1>THE PUBLIC  BROADCASTER<BR>
AND CIVIL SOCIETY</H1>
</td><td width=10><BR></td></tr></table>

<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430>
<B>Submission sections:</B>

<BR><IMG VSPACE=3 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>

<CENTER><A HREF="cox-01.html">[Changing Australia]</A> <A HREF="cox-02.html">[Political correctness and balance]</A> <A HREF="cox-03.html">[The agora or forum]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-04.html">[The ABC is not cultural spakfilla]</A> <A HREF="cox-05.html">[The metros]</A> <A HREF="cox-06.html">[Radio National (RN)]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-07.html">[Social Capital and the ABC]</A> <A HREF="cox-08.html">[The displeased piper's wanted tunes]</A><BR>
<A HREF="cox-09.html">[The ABC too timid with alternative views?]</A> <A HREF="cox-10.html">[Some proposals for changes]</A><BR>
[Marian Robinson] <A HREF="cox-mr02.html">[A two day listening sample]</A></CENTER>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=468 SRC="/../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=40><BR></td>
<td width=430><FONT SIZE=+1>
<B>This material has been prepared by Marian Robinson as part of a project as a UTS student.  Time constraints have limited the analysis and the material is presented in summary. We would like the opportunity to offer further material to the enquiry as there is more data collected than has been included. </B>
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
In this submission, I refer in particular to Radio National, which I believe should stay as it is, due to the high standards of its programming.  Radio National offers those who fund it the chance to debate social, cultural, political, and economic issues, and needs to continue to be funded at the present level to maintain its unique quality in a world of sensationalist radio journalism.  The journalistic standards of the ABC are of high quality and the programs are well researched, using qualified and often distinguished guest speakers.  This is what the Australian public have come to expect from their ABC.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Without the investment into research of the interesting range of programs on Radio National such as Radio Eye, Life Matters, Women Out Loud, Awaye, Background Briefing and Educational radio which many people in both rural and metropolitan areas rely upon - covering health, law, education, media and business,  the ABC could be reduced to covering sensationalised 'news stories', as do the commercial stations due to a lack of funding to research these valuable and informative programs.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The following is a sample of the some of the topics covered by Radio National programs  this year.   The guests on these programs are experts in their field, such as Presidents of organisations, Ministers and Professors from universities in Australia and around the world.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Life Matters:  Family  issues:   Mental illness and Mentally ill Offenders;  Rural Youth Suicide; Discipline and Children; Adoption and Reunion.
Community issues:  Violence in the community; Housing Estates.
Legal Issues:  Bill of Rights; Family Court closures.
Economic issues:   Home economics.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Background Briefing:  Political issues - The Australian First Reform Party; Anti-Asian politics in New Zetland; The Senate (behind the scenes); Indian and Pakistani politics.<BR>
Rural issues  - Calicivirus (rabbit virus)<BR>
Community issues  - The Uruguayan community in Australia; Aboriginal community development in WA; Uranium mining in Kakadu National Park.
Business issues  - Organised Crime and the Internet;  The Hunting down of the rich for tax purposes.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The Law Report: Community issues:   Legal Aid issues; Euthanasia;  Gun Control laws; Crime Prevention debate; the Constitution and the Republic;  School conflict Resolution and Mediation; Contention in Forestry; 
Family issues:  family law by computer; Children and the law; Legal Parental Responsibility; Marriage law; Children's Rights and the Family court.
International issues:  Capital punishment in the USA; Tokyo's 'Trial of the Century'; The UN;  Ireland goes to the Polls on a Legal Question; The Red Cross - Guardians of International Humanitarian Law; the Changing Nature of Crime in South Africa;  Papua New Guinea claim;  Software Pirates in China; Japanese War Crimes; Indonesia - Post War Law; the World Court.
Political issues:  Law and the Olympics;  Law and Justice policies and the Elections;  Native Title developments; Law and Order and the Federal Elections.
Medical issues:  When Law meets Medicine (medico-legal issues);  Mental illness and the Law; Nurse lawyers on Hospitals, Doctors and Health Law.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The Health Report:  Stomach cancer; AIDS vaccine; Aging and the Immune system; Colonic irrigation; Menopause; Transplanting Animal Organs into humans; Sore Throats; Breast Cancer;  Sleep disorders;  Hypnosis and Memory and Forensic Psychology; Intelligence and Common sense; Post Traumatic stress; Resilience; Emotion and Reason;  Asthma and Air Pollution; Malaria and Climate change;  Body Clocks and Brain Function.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The Education Report:  National Literacy Survey;  University Funding Cuts;  British Education Policies;  ANU's Research schools; State, Territory and Commonwealth Education Ministers' meeting;  Aboriginal culture and non-Aboriginal students; Commonwealth Ministers and education; Adult literacy; Educational Buildings; Violence in Schools; New Information Technologies; Vocational Education;  Science literacy;  Educational Journalism; School Staffing around Australia; Numeracy.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
Women Out Loud: Economic /Business issues:  Credit scheme for women in New Zetland; Community Aid Abroad program - Economic and Social progress for Indian women; Women and Unions.<BR>
Medical issues: Pre-natal testing<BR>
International women's issues:  1996 International Women's Day; Palestinian women refugees.<BR>
Community issues:: The Shoah Visual History project - Australian survivors of the holocaust;  Disability Abuse; Nuns working on the fringes of society; Growing up in ethnic communities in Australia; discrimination in Australian society.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The Business Report:  International issues: Democracy, Indonesia and Foreign Investment; Hong Kong - One Year and Counting; BHP and Ok Tedi; Business and Politics in Burma; Trading with China.<BR>
General Issues: Interest Rates, Networking in the nineties and Diamonds; Ethics and Business; The Budget Deficit; Manufacturing jobs; Corruption in High and Low Places; Banking; Reputation and Public Relations.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The Media Report:   Victorian Government Policy and Tabloid Newspapers; Murdoch's 'media empire' and the state of SBS; Using Technology to Maintain Cultural Traditions; The Changing Media Landscape in South Africa; Hindmarsh Island and "Secret Media Business"; Public Relations and the Media.
<BR><IMG VSPACE=6 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><BR>
The above material was gleaned from program reports for various days earlier this year.  They are a scattered sample with no particular dates being selected and are just included as examples of program items.  Further documentation will be available later in this project. 
</FONT>
</td></tr></table>

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="/../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
