Indonesian 'Red Beret' Special Forces arriving at Bacua airfield in November 1987 to begin a 'clean up' campaign against the resurgent Timorese resistance.  This airfield has been taken over by the Indonesian Military.  Nearby is a notorious detention and torture centre.  Indonesian troop numbers in East Timor have been estimated at about 40,000 in the period 1979 to 1981.  Current numbers are around 15,000 or more.</p>
