<font size="+1">
<center>
<h1>East Timor Images 1942 - 1996</h1>
<img src="../images/colorbar.gif"></p><br><br><br><br>
<img src="photos/matebian.jpg"></p><br>
Dawn on Mount Matebian.  In Timorese mythology the lofty Mt. Matebian (nearly 10,000 ft high) is believed to be the resting place of the souls of the dead.  Untold numbers of East Timorese died on this mountain in the early 1980's when they were forced to retreat up its side and were subjected to extensive aerial attack with bombs and napalm.  Now people participate in an annual pilgrimage to the summit in remembrance of those who died in the distant past, and the many whoses graves litter the mountain now.</p>
Ross Bird - 1995</p><br>
<img src="../images/colorbar.gif"><br><br><br>
<table width="550">
<tr>
<td align="left" valign="bottom"><a href="womsoldier.html"><img hspace=6 src="../images/tiny-logo-acij.gif">Next picture</a></td>
