</td>
<td width=20><BR></td><td ALIGN=RIGHT>
<BR><B>The ACIJ presents<BR>The Online Journalist<BR> - the <i>FREE </i>  essential web resource<BR> for journalists<BR>and those interested<BR> in the media</B><BR>
<p><p><H4> http://acij.uts.edu.au/</H4>
</td><td width=10><BR></td></tr></table>
<PRE></PRE>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=10><BR></td>
<td width=445>
The Australian Centre for Independent Journalism is fully committed to the principle that democratic societies require independent, critical and investigative journalism of the highest standard. <p>The ACIJ's aim is to promote this principle as actively and broadly as possible by supporting: <BR><LI>publication and promotion of independent, critical and investigative journalism; <BR><LI>scholarship and research into journalism nationally and internationally; and <BR><LI>community debate and discussion of issues relevant to journalism and media accountability. <p>The ACIJ is an independent non-profit journalism centre based at the University of Technology, Sydney.<p><p>
</td></tr></table>

